summary: Example test for repository-url artifact provider
description: |
    Demonstrates how to use the repository-url artifact provider.

    The repository-url provider configures external package repositories
    from .repo files or direct URLs.

    Example usage:
        prepare:
          - how: artifact
            provide:
              - repository-url:https://example.com/repo/myrepo.repo

    This test shows:
    - How to configure an external repository
    - How packages from that repository can be installed
    - Works with both .repo files and direct repository URLs
tag+:
  - provision-only
  - provision-container
adjust:
  - when: distro != fedora
    enabled: false
    because: Test uses Fedora-specific repository
